title.narrative: IMPROVED QUALITY OF CARE FROM PREGNANCYTO ADOLESCENCE FOR Maternal, Neonatal, and Child Health (MNCH) AND HIV

description.narrative: Health systems provide improved quality of care from pregnancy to adolescence for Maternal, Neonatal, and Child Health (MNCH) and HIV., which contributes to Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Young children, adolescents and women use improved and equitable high-impact maternal, newborn and child health (MNCH) and HIV services.

title.narrative: Health systems provide improved quality of care from pregnancy to adolescence for MNCH and HIV.

description.narrative: UNICEF and other partners supported the government to equip health facilities and improve the quality of services, including ensuring timely referrals and recovery from the interruption of routine services due to the COVID-19 pandemic. With direct UNICEF support, 137 health facilities received equipment for maternal, newborn and childcare. UNICEF also supported improved newborn and intrapartum care in 97 health facilities, in partnership with professional associations. UNICEF supported the strengthening of cold chain systems and made efforts to improve the quality of care for persons living with HIV, as well as rolling out mental health interventions for adolescents. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:30/12/2021
